The Eternal Father hath called himſelf The God of Peace,
                     Rom. 15.33. the Bleſſed Jeſus is The Prince of Peace;
                     Rom. 16.20. the great Legacy which he left behind Him,Iſai. 9.6. was, His Peace; and The Goſpel of Peace,
                     John 14.27. is the great

Inſtrument of Erecting that Kingdom, of which Peace is one of the greateſt Glories. Till God give his People the Bleſſing of Peace, we can't expect that Happy Time when all the ends of the Earth ſhall fear him;
                     Pſal. 67.7. and his Name will never be Hallow'd to purpoſe,Mat. 6.9, 10. nor his Will be done on Earth as it is in Heaven, till this Kingdom of his be come.

2. No Man who is fit for it, needs a Law to bring him to it.
                        Heb. 2.10. All the Soldiers of the Captain of our Salvation are Voluntiers;
                        Pſal. 110.3. and on the contrary it is certain, that he that needs a Law to bring him to it, is not fit for it.
